HEADWORD: Fishhook
<hw>Fish"hook`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A hook
for catching fish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A hook with a pendant, to the end
of which the fish-tackle is hooked.</def> <rj><au>Dana.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fishify</ent>⟦br⟧
